<div class="faqAnswer"><a name="g1">
    <b>Why did you make this?</b>
    <p>
      Check the <%#= link_to 'about', :action => 'about' %> section.  In short though, I thought it would be fun!
    </p>
</div>
<div class="faqAnswer"><a name="g3">
    <b>Why do you need my email?</b>
    <p>
    	We use email to validate you if you lose a password, and to let you know when someone has posted a comment 
			about your mugshow.  We will NEVER sell/give your email away.
    </p>
</div>
<div class="faqAnswer"><a name="g4">
    <b>Can I use a digital camera?</b>
    <p>
	    Certainly!  You can upload any image you like from a digital camera to a scan, anything really :)  
			Of course it must be an image.
    </p>
</div>
<div class="faqAnswer"><a name="g5">
    <b>Can I email in mugshots?</b>
    <p>
	    Yes!  Once you are logged in, goto 'My Mugshow' -> 'update account' for details.  
			This is great for mobile... I took my mugshot from the Brooklyn Bridge recently :) 
   </p>
</div>
<div class="faqAnswer"><a name="delete_account">
    <b>How do I delete my account?</b>
    <p>
	    To delete your account please visit <%#= link_to url = destroy_my_account_url, url %>.
   </p>
</div>
<div class="faqAnswer"><a name="r1">
    <b>What versions of Mac OS does the DMSReminder support?</b>
    <p>
      The Mac DMSReminder supports Mac OS versions 10.4.x and later.
    </p>
</div>
<div class="faqAnswer"><a name="r2">
    <b>What versions of Windows does the DMSReminder support?</b>
    <p>
      The Windows DMSReminder supports Windows versions XP.
    </p>
</div>
<div class="faqAnswer"><a name="r3">
    <b>How do I uninstall the Mac DMSReminder?</b>
    <p>
      Easy! First quit the app by clicking on the Daily Mugshot icon at the top of your screen and selecting quit.  
			Then go into your applications folder, find DMS Reminder, and drag it into your trash.  Thats it!
    </p>
</div>
<div class="faqAnswer"><a name="r4">
    <b>How do I uninstall the Windows DMSReminder?</b>
    <p>
      Easy! First quit the app by selecting the Daily Mugshot icon in your taskbar 
			(at the bottom right of your screen) choosing quit.  
			Then open Add/Remove programs from the control panel, find DMS Reminder and select uninstall.  Thats it!
    </p>
</div>

