<p>
	Your mugshow will only be featured in the search area if the 'Public' check-box in the My Sequence section is 
	checked.
</p>
</div>

<div class="faqAnswer"><a name="p4">
<b>Help! I want to retake a picture from the past.</b>
<p>
	There is no way to update pictures taken in the past.  This is done purposefully.  
	The goal of this project is to offer authentic daily snapshots, and this feature would compromise that.  
	However, if you want to remove a picture from the mugshow, you can find the thumbnail in your 'My Sequence' 
	section and uncheck it.
</p>
</div>

<div class="faqAnswer"><a name="p5">
<b>Help! I want to upload a series of pictures I took myself</b>
<p>
	There is no way to upload a batch of photos.  This is done purposefully.  
	The goal of this project is to offer authentic daily snapshots, and this feature would compromise that.
</p>
</div>

<div class="faqAnswer"><a name="p6">
<b>Help! I want to upload today's picture from a file, not a webcam</b>
<p>
	Fantastic!  When you click 'Take a Pic' from the main nav, you will be taken to a page which has a big button: 
	'Upload Pic'.  Just hit this and you are on your way!
</p>
</div>

<div class="faqAnswer"><a name="p7">
<b>Help! I want to take a second picture today</b>
<p>
	One picture per day.  Thems the rules.
</p>
</div>

<div class="faqAnswer"><a name="p8">
<b>Help! I don't have a webcam!</b>
